  "label": "Serah Tindal",
  "description": "This individual is a human woman of settled middle years, set in a compact, well-fed frame shaped by long indoor labor rather than fieldwork. Brown eyes sit beneath carefully kept blonde hair worn in a tidy shoulderl style, and taupe skin bears the faint, permanent ink-stains and shallow finger-scars typical of constant handling of cord, wax, and coin. The face is broad through the cheek with a firm jawline and fine vertical lines at the mouth, features associated with habitual bargaining and close scrutiny. The hands remain the most defining mark: thickened at the fingertips, with hardened pads and a slight bend to two knuckles from repeated lifting of trade chests and casks.",
